cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GT 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new family of objectives for adversarial training methods. It also discusses the convergence of the generator and provides sufficient conditions for local convergence. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed approach to generate higher-resolution images, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves the use of discriminators, which is a common technique in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses game theory, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
